descript.abstract: This data set shows the location of Baltimore City hospitals.
descript.purpose: The purpose of this data is to assist the City of Baltimore in identifying institutions that provides health care treatment by specialized staff and equipment. To assist the City's emergency organizations in identifying health institution during an emergency event. Cartographic, analysis, and planning.

procstep.procdesc: The data was provided in an Excel spread sheet format, which was then geocoded using EGIS's composite address locator. The geocoded results created a point shapefile, which was then reviewed to make sure each point was accurately represented. For the points that were not in the proper location; they were manually placed in the center of the buildings (CB), using the city's georeferenced serial photography (DG_200).

U.S. National Grid: This standard established a nationally consistent grid reference system, just as all street maps use a common set of street names. USNG provides a seamless plane coordinate system across jurisdictional boundaries and map scales; it enables precise position referencing with GPS, web map portals and hardcopy maps. The values found in this field locate the corresponding feature to 1m square area using USNG coordinates.
